{"key":"processedPost-12528067","value":{"id":12528067,"first":12527668,"last":12528997,"when":1273360597,"utime":"05/09/10 02:16 AM","content":"Vermiculite is a pretty good bulk substrate material.&nbsp; The first few growers who discovered this thought that verm was an inert substance and the only benefit was for holding water, as a <i>reservoir</i>, thus it was named 'rez effect'.&nbsp; We now know that verm contains minerals that are beneficial to fungi, and it can be used as a bulk substrate, either by itself or along with manure or coir, etc.<br />RR","title":"Re: rezz effect","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}